# 🐔 Poultry Disease Classification using Transfer Learning

This is an internship project that applies **transfer learning** for classifying poultry diseases using image data. The model is integrated with a **Flask web application** that allows users to upload a chicken image and receive an instant disease prediction.

## 🧪 Supported Disease Classes

- Coccidiosis  
- Salmonella  
- Newcastle Disease  
- Healthy

---

## 💡 Features

- Deep learning with MobileNetV2
- Flask web app interface
- Upload chicken images for diagnosis
- Organized project structure with HTML frontend
- Custom dataset from Kaggle

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
poultry_disease_project/
├── data/                     # Dataset folders (train, val, test)
├── static/images/           # UI images
├── templates/               # HTML templates
├── app.py                   # Flask app
├── train_model.py           # Model training script
├── model.h5                 # Saved trained model
├── best_model.h5            # (Optional) Best-performing model
├── requirements.txt         # Python dependencies
├── README.md                # Project documentation
├── data.csv                 # (Optional) dataset metadata
├── kaggle.json              # Kaggle API key
├── archive/                 # (Optional) raw zip data
├── main.ipynb               # Notebook version of app
├── pytorch-resnet18.ipynb   # (Optional) PyTorch version
└── .venv/                   # Virtual environment (optional)
```

---

## ⚙️ Installation Instructions

### 1. Clone this repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/Gayathritadiparthi/poultry-disease-classification.git
cd poultry-disease-classification
```

### 2. (Optional) Create virtual environment
```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate      # On Windows
```

### 3. Install required packages
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 4. Add dataset
Download the dataset from Kaggle:  
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/chandrashekarnatesh/poultry-diseases  
Place it under the `data/` folder and split into `train/`, `val/`, and `test/`.

### 5. Train the model
```bash
python train_model.py
```

### 6. Run the web app
```bash
python app.py
```

Open in browser: `http://127.0.0.1:5000`

---

## 🖼️ Web Pages

- `index.html` → Upload image and predict
- `predict.html` → Shows prediction result
- `about.html` → Optional info page
- `contact.html` → Optional contact page

---

